  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Alive and Smiling - Nutrition for Premature Baby</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Children and teenagers who were prematurely born have high risk of nutritional disorders; small stature, anemia, malnutrition, metabolic syndrome as well as mental, visual, hearing and coordination disorders.  Behavioral change is also a factor. Our goal is to give proper formula to all preterm babies who will come to EPM&apos;s Outpatient Care of Premature Infants. The formulas will be given for one year after breastfeeding ceases or to children who lacked breastfeeding.</narrative>
  </description>
